 Summit od Amon Hen    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">To Start I usally bid about 2 or three, most of the time pulling aragorn. But if not no big whoop.<br>
The fellowship is usally has enough archery to take out most of the minions depending on what your playing while my compainons are usally beefed up to take on the rest. The allies are the latest addition to the deck except Elrond which I cut dwon one to make room for the other allies. The allies are a big boost for the deck I feel more confadent double jumping more often. While Sam and thrarin provide nice meals for Balrogs and other such minions theres not a lot that can dent my fellowship.<br>
     My shadow is one of a kind of at least that I&#39;ve seen. It provides the moria adding capabilty while the monster Uruks take advantage of it. When playing my shadow I usally save my moria scouts and goblin runners for site 5 playing a few of them so not to clutter my hand. I always play my conditions as soon as I get them cause there A key part for the shadow to work well like any moria deck basicaly. But I find out that I usally get out more minions on a conctant bases(usally around nine or so) than in a &quot;normal&quot; swarms deck. Sure a cave troll is intemidating but so is a few runners and scouts with a lurtz and a troop. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
